Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Halve and peel the @red onion{1}. Chop each half into four wedges. Pop the potato and onion onto a large #baking tray{} (use two if cooking for 3 or 4 people!). Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat. Place on the top shelf of the oven to roast until tender and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Meanwhile, drain the @sweetcorn{326} in a #sieve{}. Heat a large #frying pan{} over high heat (no oil). When the pan is really hot, add the sweetcorn. Cook, stirring occasionally and gently shaking the pan until the corn is charred, about ~{4%minutes}.

> TIP: Don't move it too much or it won't char properly.

When charred, remove the pan from the heat.

While your corn is charring, halve the @red chilli{1/2} lengthways, deseed then thinly slice. Roughly chop the @coriander{1} (stalks and all). Crumble the @Feta Cheese{100} into small pieces using your hands. Halve the @lime{1}.

Next, pop the @miso paste{15}, @honey{15}, @wholegrain mustard{1/2} and @olive oil{2} into a small #bowl{}. Squeeze in the juice from the lime and whisk well to combine. Set to one side.

When the wedges and onion are cooked, remove from the oven and add the charred sweetcorn and @chopped kale{100} to the baking tray. There's a lot, but don't worry - it'll wilt down in the oven! Gently mix the kale through the veggies and return to the oven for ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: Use two large spoons to do this!

Once out of the oven, tip the roasted veggies into a #mixing bowl{} and stir through half the dressing. Share between your bowls. Top with the feta, coriander, sliced chilli and @pumpkin seeds{15} and drizzle over the remaining dressing. Enjoy!